spec: hashlib_extra153
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(hashlib)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/hashlib.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/hashlib.html — Python hashlib module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/hashlib.py"
    - "CPython source: Modules/_hashlib.c"
    - "hashlib_extra152.zspec.zsdl — covers hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('md5'/'sha256'/'sha512'/'new'/'algorithms_guaranteed'/'algorithms_available'/'file_digest') / hashlib.__dict__.__len__()==33 / hashlib.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('dict') (table + invariants)."
    - "hashlib_extra151.zspec.zsdl — covers hashlib._hashlib.HASH.update/__qualname__.__eq__('HASH.update') / HASH.digest/__qualname__.__eq__('HASH.digest') / HASH.hexdigest/__qualname__.__eq__('HASH.hexdigest') / HASH.copy/__qualname__.__eq__('HASH.copy') / HASH.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') / HASH.__dict__.__len__()==10 (table + invariants)."
    - "hashlib_extra150.zspec.zsdl — covers hashlib._hashlib.__name__.__eq__('_hashlib') / _hashlib.__spec__.name.__eq__('_hashlib') / _hashlib.__loader__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('ExtensionFileLoader') / _hashlib.__package__.__eq__('') / _hashlib.HASH.__name__/__module__/__qualname__ equality / hashlib.__loader__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('SourceFileLoader') / hashlib.__package__.__eq__('') (table + invariants)."
    - "hashlib_extra149.zspec.zsdl — covers hashlib.__all__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('tuple') / __all__.__len__()==19 / __all__.__contains__ checks (table + invariants)."
    - "hashlib_extra148.zspec.zsdl — covers hashlib.file_digest/__qualname__/__module__/__class__.__name__ / __code__.co_argcount==2 / hashlib.__spec__.name.__eq__('hashlib') / hashlib.__doc__.__len__()==2098 (table + invariants)."
    - "hashlib_extra99.zspec.zsdl — covers md5/sha1/sha224/sha256/sha384/sha512 constructor __class__.__name__ and __name__ equality / algorithms_guaranteed.__len__()==14."
    - "hashlib.zspec / early extras — cover hashlib.__name__/__package__ (base spec)."
  notes:
    - "This spec does NOT duplicate invariants present in hashlib_extra95 through hashlib_extra152."
    - "Wave 329 theme: _hashlib C extension module namespace — _hashlib.__dict__.__len__()==32 / _hashlib.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('dict') / _hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('HMAC') / _hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('HASHXOF') / _hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('compare_digest') / _hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('hmac_digest') / _hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('openssl_sha3_256') / _hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('scrypt'). Also size comparison: hashlib(33) vs _hashlib(32) — the public wrapper has exactly 1 more entry than the C extension."
    - "_hashlib.__dict__.__len__() == 32. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "_hashlib.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'dict'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('HMAC') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('HASHXOF') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('compare_digest') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('hmac_digest') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('openssl_sha3_256') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('scrypt') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Note: _hashlib.__dict__.__len__() == 32. The 32 C extension entries include: HASH, HASHXOF, HMAC, UnsupportedDigestmodError (4 types), _GIL_MINSIZE, __doc__, __file__, __loader__, __name__, __package__, __spec__ (6 metadata), _constructors, compare_digest, get_fips_mode, hmac_digest, hmac_new, new, pbkdf2_hmac, scrypt (8 functions), openssl_md5, openssl_md_meth_names, openssl_sha1, openssl_sha224, openssl_sha256, openssl_sha384, openssl_sha3_224, openssl_sha3_256, openssl_sha3_384, openssl_sha3_512, openssl_sha512, openssl_shake_128, openssl_shake_256 (13 openssl entries). The public hashlib module dict (33) has exactly 1 more entry than _hashlib (32), because hashlib adds the top-level _hashlib reference itself."
    - "Note: _hashlib.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'dict' (4 chars). Like all other module __dict__ objects (hashlib, struct, uuid, socket, _struct, _socket), the _hashlib C extension module dict is a plain mutable dict. This contrasts with _hashlib.HASH.__dict__ (mappingproxy, 12 chars) — the C extension type's class dict is a read-only mappingproxy."
    - "Note: The _hashlib C extension exposes HMAC (C-level HMAC type) and HASHXOF (C-level XOF/extendable-output-function type) alongside HASH. extra151 anchors HASH.__dict__.__len__()==10 and HASH.__dict__.__class__.__name__=='mappingproxy'; this spec anchors HMAC and HASHXOF as _hashlib dict members."
    - "Note: compare_digest and hmac_digest are two security-focused functions in _hashlib. compare_digest performs a constant-time comparison of two digests to prevent timing attacks. hmac_digest computes an HMAC digest in a single call, combining hmac_new + digest into one efficient C-level operation."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# _hashlib.__dict__.__len__()==32
# _hashlib.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('dict')
# hashlib.__dict__.__len__()==33
#
# Wave 329 theme: _hashlib C extension namespace size vs public hashlib size.
#
# The _hashlib C extension dict (32 entries) is exactly 1 entry smaller than the
# public hashlib module dict (33 entries). This 1-entry difference arises because
# hashlib adds the '_hashlib' reference to itself in its own module namespace.
# Both dicts have __class__.__name__ == 'dict' (4 chars) — plain mutable module dicts.
# extra152 anchors hashlib.__dict__.__len__()==33 as a table and standalone; no prior
# hashlib spec anchors _hashlib.__dict__.__len__()==32 as a table under hashhc153.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table hashlib_extra153.hashlib_vs_hashlib_c_dict_sizes:
  description: "_hashlib.__dict__.__len__()==32 / _hashlib.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('dict')==True / hashlib.__dict__.__len__()==33 — _hashlib C extension dict (32) is exactly 1 entry smaller than the public hashlib dict (33); the 1-entry difference is the '_hashlib' self-reference added by hashlib; both dicts are plain 'dict' (4 chars), not mappingproxy; extra152 anchors hashlib dict len; first hashhc153 anchor for _hashlib dict len and the comparison"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: identity
  id_prefix: hashhc153

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [hashlib_c_dict_len_32,   "_hashlib.__dict__.__len__",                    [],      32, "_hashlib.__dict__.__len__() is 32 (C extension dict; 1 fewer than hashlib's 33 entries)"]
    - [hashlib_c_dict_class,    "_hashlib.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__",  ["dict"], true, "_hashlib.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'dict' (4 chars; plain mutable module dict, same as hashlib)"]
    - [hashlib_dict_len_33,     "__dict__.__len__",                             [],      33, "hashlib.__dict__.__len__() is 33 (public wrapper; 1 more than _hashlib because of the '_hashlib' self-reference)"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# _hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('HMAC')
# _hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('HASHXOF')
# _hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('compare_digest')
# _hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('hmac_digest')
#
# Wave 329 theme: _hashlib contains security-focused types and functions.
#
# HMAC (C-level HMAC type), HASHXOF (C-level XOF type), compare_digest (constant-time
# comparison), and hmac_digest (single-call HMAC computation) are four security-focused
# entries in _hashlib.__dict__. extra151 anchors HASH (the standard hash type); no prior
# hashlib spec anchors HMAC, HASHXOF, compare_digest, or hmac_digest as a table under
# hashhc153. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table hashlib_extra153.hashlib_c_dict_security_entries:
  description: "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('HMAC')==True / __dict__.__contains__('HASHXOF')==True / __dict__.__contains__('compare_digest')==True / __dict__.__contains__('hmac_digest')==True — HMAC is the C-level HMAC type; HASHXOF is the extendable-output-function type (shake_128/shake_256); compare_digest does constant-time comparison to prevent timing attacks; hmac_digest is a single-call HMAC combining hmac_new + digest; all are C-level; extra151 anchors HASH; first hashhc153 anchor for these four entries"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: identity
  id_prefix: hashhc153

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [hashlib_c_HMAC,            "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__",  ["HMAC"],            true, "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('HMAC') == True (C-level HMAC type alongside HASH and HASHXOF)"]
    - [hashlib_c_HASHXOF,         "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__",  ["HASHXOF"],         true, "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('HASHXOF') == True (C-level XOF type for shake_128/shake_256 extendable output)"]
    - [hashlib_c_compare_digest,  "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__",  ["compare_digest"],  true, "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('compare_digest') == True (constant-time digest comparison; prevents timing attacks)"]
    - [hashlib_c_hmac_digest,     "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__",  ["hmac_digest"],     true, "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('hmac_digest') == True (single-call HMAC: combines hmac_new + digest efficiently)"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# _hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('openssl_sha3_256')
# _hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('scrypt')
# _hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('new')
#
# Wave 329 theme: _hashlib contains openssl-prefixed constructors and key functions.
#
# openssl_sha3_256 is one of 11 openssl_* prefixed hash constructor functions in _hashlib.
# scrypt is the memory-hard key derivation function (KDF) exposed at the C level.
# new is the generic hash constructor (the C-level equivalent of hashlib.new).
# No prior hashlib spec anchors these three as a table under hashhc153.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table hashlib_extra153.hashlib_c_dict_openssl_and_kdf_entries:
  description: "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('openssl_sha3_256')==True / __dict__.__contains__('scrypt')==True / __dict__.__contains__('new')==True — openssl_sha3_256 is one of 13 openssl_* prefixed constructors in _hashlib (openssl_md5/sha1/sha224/sha256/sha384/sha512/sha3_224/sha3_256/sha3_384/sha3_512/shake_128/shake_256 + openssl_md_meth_names); scrypt is the memory-hard KDF; new is the generic C-level constructor; no prior hashlib spec anchors these under hashhc153"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: identity
  id_prefix: hashhc153

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [hashlib_c_openssl_sha3_256,  "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__",  ["openssl_sha3_256"],  true, "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('openssl_sha3_256') == True (one of 11 openssl_* SHA-3 and SHA-2 constructors)"]
    - [hashlib_c_scrypt,            "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__",  ["scrypt"],            true, "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('scrypt') == True (memory-hard key derivation function; requires OpenSSL)"]
    - [hashlib_c_new,               "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__",  ["new"],               true, "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('new') == True (generic C-level hash constructor accepting algorithm name)"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# _hashlib.__dict__.__len__()==32 — standalone
#
# _hashlib.__dict__.__len__() is 32. The 32 C extension entries are: 4 types (HASH,
# HASHXOF, HMAC, UnsupportedDigestmodError), 6 metadata entries (__name__, __doc__,
# __file__, __loader__, __package__, __spec__), 1 private entry (_GIL_MINSIZE), 1 private
# list (_constructors), 8 functions (compare_digest, get_fips_mode, hmac_digest, hmac_new,
# new, pbkdf2_hmac, scrypt, openssl_md_meth_names), and 12 openssl_* hash constructors
# (openssl_md5, openssl_sha1, openssl_sha224, openssl_sha256, openssl_sha384,
# openssl_sha3_224, openssl_sha3_256, openssl_sha3_384, openssl_sha3_512, openssl_sha512,
# openssl_shake_128, openssl_shake_256). The public hashlib (33) has 1 more entry.
# No prior hashlib spec anchors _hashlib.__dict__.__len__()==32 as a standalone under
# hashhc153. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant hashlib_extra153.hashlib_c_dict_len_32:
  description: "_hashlib.__dict__.__len__() == 32 — 32 C extension entries: 4 types (HASH/HASHXOF/HMAC/UnsupportedDigestmodError) + 6 metadata + 1 _GIL_MINSIZE + 1 _constructors + 8 functions (compare_digest/get_fips_mode/hmac_digest/hmac_new/new/pbkdf2_hmac/scrypt/openssl_md_meth_names) + 12 openssl_* constructors; public hashlib(33) = _hashlib(32) + 1; no prior hashlib spec anchors this as a standalone; first standalone under hashhc153"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "_hashlib.__dict__.__len__"
  args: []
  expected: 32

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# _hashlib.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('dict') — standalone
#
# _hashlib.__dict__.__class__.__name__ is 'dict' (4 chars). Like all module __dict__
# objects, the _hashlib C extension module dict is a plain mutable dict. This is
# distinct from the _hashlib.HASH.__dict__ which is a mappingproxy (12 chars, anchored
# in extra151). The plain 'dict' type applies to all module-level dicts regardless of
# whether the module is a pure-Python module (hashlib) or a C extension (_hashlib).
# No prior hashlib spec anchors _hashlib.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('dict')
# as a standalone under hashhc153. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant hashlib_extra153.hashlib_c_dict_class_dict:
  description: "_hashlib.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('dict') == True — 'dict' (4 chars); C extension module dicts are plain mutable dicts, same as pure-Python module dicts (hashlib); contrasts with _hashlib.HASH.__dict__ (mappingproxy, 12 chars, extra151); pattern: all module __dict__ are 'dict', all class __dict__ are 'mappingproxy'; no prior hashlib spec anchors this as a standalone; first standalone under hashhc153"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "_hashlib.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__"
  args: ["dict"]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# _hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('HMAC') — standalone
#
# _hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('HMAC') is True. _hashlib.HMAC is a C-level type
# for computing HMAC (Hash-based Message Authentication Code) values. It provides
# the same interface as the HASH type but incorporates a secret key, making the
# digest value depend on both the message content and the key. extra151 anchors
# _hashlib.HASH (the standard hash type); no prior hashlib spec anchors
# _hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('HMAC') as a standalone under hashhc153.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant hashlib_extra153.hashlib_c_dict_contains_HMAC:
  description: "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('HMAC') == True — C-level HMAC type; computes Hash-based Message Authentication Codes; digest depends on message + secret key; three C types in _hashlib: HASH (extra151) + HASHXOF + HMAC; no prior hashlib spec anchors this as a standalone; first standalone under hashhc153"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__"
  args: ["HMAC"]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# _hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('compare_digest') — standalone
#
# _hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('compare_digest') is True. _hashlib.compare_digest
# (also accessible as hmac.compare_digest) performs a constant-time comparison of
# two byte strings or ASCII strings. It takes the same amount of time regardless of
# how many bytes match, preventing timing side-channel attacks where an attacker
# could guess the correct digest byte-by-byte by measuring comparison time.
# No prior hashlib spec anchors _hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('compare_digest')
# as a standalone under hashhc153. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant hashlib_extra153.hashlib_c_dict_contains_compare_digest:
  description: "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('compare_digest') == True — constant-time comparison of two digests; prevents timing side-channel attacks (comparison time independent of byte match count); also accessible as hmac.compare_digest; C-level implementation in Modules/_hashlib.c; no prior hashlib spec anchors this as a standalone; first standalone under hashhc153"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__"
  args: ["compare_digest"]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# _hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('scrypt') — standalone
#
# _hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('scrypt') is True. _hashlib.scrypt is the C-level
# implementation of the scrypt key derivation function (KDF). scrypt is a memory-hard
# KDF designed to be expensive in both CPU and memory, making brute-force attacks
# against password hashes computationally infeasible even with specialized hardware.
# It is exposed at the public level as hashlib.scrypt. extra152 anchors
# hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('scrypt')==True (the public wrapper entry); no prior
# hashlib spec anchors _hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('scrypt') as a standalone
# under hashhc153. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant hashlib_extra153.hashlib_c_dict_contains_scrypt:
  description: "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('scrypt') == True — memory-hard KDF (key derivation function); expensive in CPU and RAM; resists brute-force even with GPUs/ASICs; public hashlib.scrypt delegates to this C-level function; extra152 anchors hashlib.__dict__.__contains__('scrypt'); no prior hashlib spec anchors this as a standalone; first standalone under hashhc153"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "_hashlib.__dict__.__contains__"
  args: ["scrypt"]
  expected: true
